==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Finality
<hw>Fi*nal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Finalities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>finalitas</ets>
the being last.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being final,
finished, or complete; a final or conclusive arrangement; a
settlement.</def> <rj><au>Baxter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The relation of end or purpose to its means.</def>
<rj><au>Janet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>finalization</ent>⟦br⟧
